      "date": "2019-06-19 03:42:04.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n(1 comment)\n\nShouldn't this patch also remove cfs_get_random_bytes() from libcfs now that it is unused?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "1fc1313a571cfcb47c38a4c1e8e58ce36169c6dc",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 805,
        "name": "Neil Brown",
        "email": "neil@brown.name",
        "username": "neilbrown"
      },
      "date": "2019-06-19 04:16:25.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nJames is doing it as two separate patches because that is they way I did it upstream.  The next patch (508d5e0f4d45) removes a lot more than just cfs_get_random_bytes().\n\nIt is frustrating that we are drip-feed the patches rather than seeing a whole series together, but that is one of the drawbacks of forcing everything through gerrit, it seems.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "98967b75a8621b3295b72957328518967417b711",
      "author": {
